  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study hypothesis: in groups receiving tailored education and feedback in a style that
      matches their psychological profile, will show a higher CPAP adherence rates than groups
      receiving mismatched tailored education / feedback, and groups that receive no tailored
      education and feedback (standard of care).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Three group, randomized, controlled clinical trial assessing the extent to which tailoring a
      CPAP intervention entailing education and feedback to the psychological profile of new CPAP
      users can enhance the impact of the intervention in terms of adherence-related behavior.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
